</center>

## Superfish

Here are some articles about superfish:  

[_Komodia/Superfish SSL Validation is Broken_](https://blog.filippo.io/komodia-superfish-ssl-validation-is-broken/), Filippo Valsorda  
[_Extracting the SuperFish certificate_](http://blog.erratasec.com/2015/02/extracting-superfish-certificate.html), Robert Graham  
[_Lenovo Under Sustained Man in Middle Management Attack_](http://bitbanter.com/2015/02/20/lenovo-man-middle/), Josh Cincinatti  
[_You Had One Job, Lenovo_](http://www.slate.com/articles/technology/bitwise/2015/02/lenovo_superfish_scandal_why_it_s_one_of_the_worst_consumer_computing_screw.html), David Auerbach, Slate  

## SSL Warings

[Adrienne Felt](http://research.google.com/pubs/AdrienneFelt.html)'s work on SSL warnings in Chrome browser:  
[_Improving SSL Warnings_](https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1TNFx6eaQVfe83PV80-FZ39QY1dSLGCWW8f2i5-NeJ48/edit#slide=id.p) (talk slides)  
[_Improving SSL Warnings: Comprehension and Adherence_](http://static.googleusercontent.com/media/research.google.com/en/us/pubs/archive/43265.pdf)  
[_Experimenting At Scale With Google Chrome's SSL Warning_](http://static.googleusercontent.com/media/research.google.com/en/us/pubs/archive/41927.pdf)  
You can also see her old page about the work she did at UVa: [_Privacy Protection for Social Network APIs_](http://www.cs.virginia.edu/felt/privacy/).
